flag.description: Contains characteristics of an identified security risk.

known_threat.name: Trojan-Downloader.Agent!sd6
known_threat.description: Trojan-Downloader.Agent!sd6 attempts to download malicious files to the local computer and execute them.

known_threat.name: Hacktool.Rootkit!sd6
known_threat.description: Hacktool.Rootkit!sd6 is a malicious application that could be used by attackers to break into a system.

known_threat.name: Trojan.KillAV!sd6
known_threat.description: Trojan.KillAV!sd6 is a malicious program that does not infect other files but may represents security risk for your computer and/or network environment.

known_threat.name: Adware.Component.Unrelated
known_threat.description: These common components have files and keys that are in different threats but the threats are not related to one another in that the author of the signature is not the same. It is recommended that all these entries be removed.

notes_collection.note: %Temp% is a variable that refers to the temporary folder in the short path form. By default, this is C:\Documents and Settings\[UserName]\Local Settings\Temp\ (Windows NT/2000/XP).
%System% is a variable that refers to the System folder. By default, this is C:\Windows\System (Windows 95/98/Me), C:\Winnt\System32 (Windows NT/2000), or C:\Windows\System32 (Windows XP).
[generic host process filename] is a full path filename of [generic host process].
so that scvhost.exe runs every time Windows starts
